content.description: Start on good crimps and head up though nice edges to an easy mantle.
content.location: Directly behind Filla Void. See pic.

content.description: Stand start on broken jugs just left of the tree poking out of the boulder. Follow the flake and broken edges to the top through some suspect rock.
content.location: Directly behind Filla Void. See pic.

content.description: Start on slanted crimps and negotiate a blank prow to jugs. Pulling on is half the battle...
content.location: North facing arete on the Blue-eyed Boulder

content.description:
A stellar line of pockets!

Several variations exist, my personal favorite uses two monos :)

Fun line to a nice mantel
content.protection: Landing is a bit awkward, 2 pads should cover it
content.location: Sit/squat start in the left-most pair of pockets just above Blue Eyed, and make fun moves through the pockets to the right. About 3 moves in, you can go up with your left to a decent mono(and them move to another mono with your right), or make an awkward left cross to a slightly better hold. Easy topout, just find the pocket in the back.

content.description: Stand start on good incut flake. Head up edges to an easy mantle.
content.location: Directly behind Filla Void. See pic.

content.description: Small edges lead to a spicy top out.

This arete faces uphill and can't be seen from the road. Start with your righthand on the only edge while your lefthand will be slapping up the arete using small edges. At the crux the feet disappear and the finish jug is in sight but out of reach. It is at this point that the name of the problem seems to make total sense.
content.location: This problem is located up on the western hillside 1.4 miles up Cottonwood Rd. It's a larger boulder and can be seen from the road if you know what to look for. The Beautiful arete that you slap up with your left hand while climbing Filla Void is the right side as you see it from the road. The boulders in this area are located on the hillside up above the the wash which contains the fast twitch boulders.

content.description: Stand start to the right of a small tree. Mantle onto the slab and head to the top on some suspect edges. There was a lot of lichen on the holds and feet. Doesn’t get done much, likely due to the spooky fall if you slipped off.
content.protection: Route is easy but protection is not great
content.location: If looking directly at Blue Eyed, look to climbers right and you will see the backside of the boulder 50 feet to the north of you.  See pic of problem.

content.description: Yall thought you was coming to Engine Creek? NAW. This things small, not splitter and dynamic so sit yo ass down in a right facin flake. Lie back,  work up dis n' fire a thugged-out dynamic move up ta tha jug above n' top up on easy as f*ck terrain feelin like da boss.
content.protection: A single medium sized pad if you a'scard
content.location: On the right side of The Prow, right of the arete.

content.description: Sit start matched on good rail, big move to good and sloping pockets, go up towards giant hole/pocket, tecky mantel.
content.location: On a boulder up hill from filla void named The Prow, starts on left side of boulder
